Refer to the figure <image 1>, Which term refers to the follows the exposition where the conflict is introduced?

A. falling action
B. climax
C. exposition
D. rising action

The term that refers to the part of the plot that follows the exposition where the conflict is introduced is:

D. rising action

In the image, the rising action is represented by the line that slopes upward from the left to the peak, indicating an increase in tension and development of the conflict. The orange arrow points to this part of the graph, which corresponds to the rising action.
